---

## 1. Main Container

This is the top-level wrapper that holds the two main columns of the page.

* **Main Element:** `<div>`
* **Key Class:** `main-container`

---

## 2. Left Panel (Branding/Title)

This section acts as the left-hand column, likely for branding, a title, or a welcome message.

* **Main Element:** `<div>`
* **Key Class:** `left-panel`
* **Sub-components:**
    * `<h2>`: The main heading "Sign Up".
    * `<p>`: A sub-heading or instruction.

---

## 3. Form Container (Main Interaction)

This is the right-hand column that contains the actual sign-up form.

* **Main Element:** `<div>`
* **Key Class:** `form-container`
* **Sub-components:**
    * `<form>`: The main form element.
        * **ID:** `signupForm` (This is the **key selector** your JavaScript will use to catch the 'submit' event).
    * **Input Groups:** The form contains **4 identical** `div.input-group` elements. This is a common pattern for styling labels and inputs together.
        * **Structure of each `div.input-group`:**
            * `<input>`: The text field. Each has a unique `id` (e.g., `name`, `email`), a `name` attribute (for sending data), and is set to `required`.
            * `<label>`: The label for the input. The `for` attribute (e.g., `for="name"`) correctly matches the input's `id`.
    * `<button type="submit">`: The main "Sign Up" button that submits the form.
    * `<p class="text-center">`: A paragraph *after* the form.
        * `<a>`: A link pointing to the login page (`/login`).

---

## 4. Assets & Scripts

These are the external files loaded at the end of the `<body>`.

* **CSS:**
    * `/css/signup.css`: The custom stylesheet that defines all the classes above.
* **JavaScript:**
    * `axios.min.js`: The Axios library for making API requests (this will be used to send the form data to your server).
    * `/js/config.js`: (Likely contains your `BASE_URL` or other configuration).
    * `/js/signup.js`: The script that will handle the `signupForm` submission, send the data with Axios, and redirect the user.